CVitae is a full-stack AI-powered resume optimization platform that transforms master resumes into targeted, ATS-optimized resumes using Groq AI and Jake's LaTeX formatting. The application features a minimalist black & white design with smooth animations and integrated AI assistance.

Technology Stack & Architecture
Backend (Java Spring Boot)
Main Application: CVitaeApplication.java
Controllers:
ResumeController.java - Resume generation, job analysis, file uploads
ChatController.java - AI chatbot interactions and suggestions
ExportController.java - PDF/PNG/JPG export functionality
Services:
GroqAIServiceImpl.java - Groq AI integration for resume optimization
ResumeServiceImpl.java - Core resume processing logic
ExportServiceImpl.java - Multi-format export handling
ChatServiceImpl.java - AI conversation management
Data Models:
Resume.java - Resume entity with JPA
entity/ChatMessage.java - Chat history persistence
dto/ folder - 12 DTOs for API requests/responses
Frontend (React TypeScript)
Main App: App.tsx - Route configuration with Framer Motion
Pages:
HomePage.tsx - Hero section with features and call-to-action
ResumeBuilderPage.tsx - 4-step wizard (upload, job details, settings, generation)
ExportPage.tsx - Multi-format download interface
AboutPage.tsx - Company information and technology showcase
Components:
ChatBot.tsx - AI assistant with conversation interface
Layout.tsx - Main layout with header and navigation
Header.tsx & Footer.tsx - Site structure components
LaTeX Service (Python Flask)
Core Service: app.py - LaTeX compilation microservice
Features: PDF generation, image conversion, Jake's template formatting
Deployment & Infrastructure
Docker Configuration: docker-compose.dev.yml - Multi-service orchestration
Services: PostgreSQL database, backend API, frontend UI, LaTeX compiler
Production Setup: docker-compose.prod.yml with NGINX reverse proxy
Key Features & Functionality
Core Resume Processing
AI Analysis: Job posting keyword extraction and ATS optimization
Smart Tailoring: Master resume content adaptation to job requirements
Multi-format Export: PDF, PNG, JPG, and raw LaTeX code downloads
File Upload Support: PDF, DOCX, and text file processing
User Interface
Progressive Web Design: 4-step resume builder workflow
Real-time Chat: AI assistant for resume improvement suggestions
Drag & Drop: File upload with visual feedback
Responsive Design: Tailwind CSS with mobile-first approach
AI Integration
Groq AI Service: LLaMA model integration for intelligent resume optimization
Conversation Context: Persistent chat sessions for iterative improvements
ATS Optimization: Keyword matching and formatting recommendations
Database Schema
Resumes Table: User data, job postings, generated content, LaTeX code
Chat Messages: Conversation history and AI responses
Supabase Integration: PostgreSQL with real-time capabilities
Development & Testing
Comprehensive Testing: TESTING.md - Full testing checklist for all endpoints
Docker Development: docker-compose.dev.yml - Local development environment
Production Ready: Complete CI/CD pipeline with debugging documentation
This codebase represents a production-ready, enterprise-grade AI resume application with full-stack TypeScript/Java implementation, containerized deployment, and comprehensive testing coverage.
